local storage :::

- if you want to store your data in nodes or kubernetes cluster 
- we use directory storatge 
- default storage path is /opt/local-path-provisioner
- if your pod is running worker1 in this pvc store your data in worker1 /opt/local-path-provisioner or smilier your worker2 is haveing pod in that
  case all pod that using pvc maintain his own node. 
- in this you can store your data in your local hard disk 
- when you have amount of disk in your local system and you wnat to use internal storage 
- don't need to setup any external storage like NFS samba or others 
- mostly if you build your on-premise local setup in your office or local machines 

- this is provided by rancher github link is  ::: https://github.com/rancher/local-path-provisioner 
- installation link is :::  kubectl apply -f https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rancher/local-path-provisioner/v0.0.34/deploy/local-path-storage.yaml
- if you want to change dir path like /opt rplace with /data so 
- wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rancher/local-path-provisioner/v0.0.34/deploy/local-path-storage.yaml  and edit this replce path with your own path 

